<br>
So what ruined it in the end? People wanted to debate minor details in the tactics channel we'd set up, people started threatening to leave if we didn't get the groups list made faster, people wanted groups made up to their specifications/friends, etc. And while you're probably thinking this is only to be expected for an open raid with a last-minute change of leadership, the sad fact is this is pretty common with most open raids and even guild raids.<br>
<br>
The bottom line is, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> raids cannot be run by democracy</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. There aren't enough hours in the day.  Sometimes the absolute best thing you can do to help ensure a raid's success is shut up and leave the leaders alone.  Getting a decision *made* is more important than spending two hours making sure it's the absolute right decision to within ten decimal places. If you see someone about to make a clear mistake, that's one thing. If it's just an opinion, ask yourself if it's really worth bringing everything to a grinding halt to debate it. And I do practice what I preach; when I go on open raids (i.e., just as one of the troops), I try to do my job, leave the raid leader alone unless I absolutely need to know the answer to a question, and follow instructions (whether or not I agree with them 100%). <br>
<br>
There were also other minor problems - one wizard who was supposed to be on the raid decided to leave the zone, the channel, and go perma-AFK (and this was before any problems started - I'm not impressed). We had no experienced Hate pullers. But we had 5+ groups of people who were 50+, including four clerics and many enchanters, there was absolutely no reason we couldn't go up there and kill some stuff, it just required some cooperation.<br>
<br>
The frequent open raids are one of the really cool things about this server; I'd just like to raise people's awareness a little bit about what a pain it is to lead one. I understand this was an unusual situation, but this stuff happens all the time. So, in short... Unless you want to be the one up there taking all the heat, be patient, and cut your raid leader some slack. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
(To those of you who *were* enthusiastic and willing to cooperate, I'm really sorry - I really wanted to pull this off for you. I should have tried a little harder to deal with the dissension, I'm just a little rusty in the &quot;leadership&quot; role and it was obvious that at least a few people weren't thrilled with the situation after Nueelien couldn't show.)<br>
<br>
Looking forward to next time,<br>
 <p>Gwynne Athelas<br>
54th Cleric of Tunare<br>
